Insertion functions
    insert # will insert at any position.
        insert(1, "trial")
    append # will append to the last. 
        append("last")

removal functinons
    pop
        pop(0)
        pop(1)

    del
        But this one is on the list. 
        del people_dinner[0]

    remove
        removing by value. 
        example: people.remove("value")

Sorting functions
    On the array 
        sort() # Permanantly sort the array. 
            can also be used to sort in reverse order by specifying reverse=True
            example: cars.sort(reverse=True)
        sorted() # Will only return the sorted array but will not not alter the array itself. 
            can also be used to sort list in reverse list. 
            example : sorted(cars, reverse=True)
        reverse() # will reverse the order of the list. 


length of the array. 
len(cars)


Accessing the elements of the array. 
by index 
my_array[0]
my_array[1]

to modify an element of an array it  will use. 
my_array[0] = "new val"

String Functions. 
    upper() = makes string upper case. 
    lower() = makes string lower case. 

String formatter: 
    Using string formatter you can include varibles in double quotes. 
    any_string = "hello world
    f"My String is {any_string}"
    Another example you can invoke a function 
    f"String in upper case is {any_string.upper()} uppercased"

Looping constructs. 
    for var in list: 
        print(var)    

